- **[w2](./W2/)**, *Introduction to Python*
- **[w3](./W3/)**, *Functions and Files*
- **[w4](./W4/)**, *Intro to OOP Python*
- **[w5](./W5/)**, *Inheritance and Polymorphism*
- **[w6](./W6/)**, *Abstract, Interface, and Exceptions*
- **[Revision](./revision/)**, *Revision Project*

## Weekly structure

Each week provides:
1. A `README.md` summarizing the lecture topics and learning objectives,
2. Exercise prompts designed for a 2-hour lab session,
3. An assignment that is due in the following week.

## Course project

A small project will be completed at the end of the course. The project will require the application of object-oriented design, file handling, and basic error management. See the **[project](./project/)** folder when available.

## Notes

Materials are provided as-is. There may be mistakes, improvements are welcome through issues and pull requests.
